wlanpi-shell-config (1.1.2) bookworm; urgency=medium

  * Add manual tmux session persistence (Prefix+Ctrl-s/Ctrl-r)
  * Implement checksum-based config management for safe upgrades
  * Optimize tmux for WLAN Pi use (25k scrollback, 15s refresh)
  * Refactor status bar to use helper scripts
  * Add configurable user support via /etc/default/wlanpi-shell-config
  * Fix: Move tmux choose-tree binding to Prefix+T (was Prefix+Ctrl-s)
  * Behavior: Package upgrades now auto-update unmodified user configs
  * Behavior: State files preserved on remove, deleted only on purge

 -- Josh Schmelzle <josh@joshschmelzle.com>  Sun, 25 Jan 2026 14:45:57 -0500

wlanpi-shell-config (1.1.1) bookworm; urgency=medium

  * Bundle fzf shell integration (key-bindings and completion)
  * Fixes ctrl-r fzf history search when docs are stripped
  * Add fallback to system fzf files if bundled files are missing
  * Move fzf from Recommends to Depends (ensures fzf is always installed)
  * Move xclip from Recommends to Suggests (optional clipboard support)

